South Korea â€™s 30 biggest industrial
groups plan to increase total spending, including capital
expenditure, research and development and acquisitions, by 12
percent in 2012 from last year.  Spending for the groups, including  Samsung Group  and  LG
Group , will rise to a record 151.4 trillion won ($131 billion),
the Ministry of Knowledge Economy said in an e-mailed statement
after a meeting with executives. The groups will hire 123,000
new workers, up 2.2 percent from 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
